    • addPhotoCollection

      public void addPhotoCollection(Photo photo)
      This method updates photoCollection when a photo is added to an album. If a photo is added with a new caption or new tags to an album, the photo in photoCollection is updated to reflect these changes. Photo.numAlbumsContaining is incremented by 1, as this method is only ever called when a photo is being added to an album for the first time.
      Parameters:
      photo - the Photo that was added

    • removePhotoCollection

      public void removePhotoCollection(String name)
      This method updates photoCollection when a photo is deleted from an album. This method is run if a photo is deleted from an album or an album containing photos is deleted. Photo.numAlbumsContaining is decremented by 1. If this value hits 0, then no albums contain the photo, so its information is wiped from photoCollection. This will "reset" the photo, if it is added again in the future.
      Parameters:
      name - of the Photo that was deleted

    • getPhotoIndex

      public int getPhotoIndex(Photo photo)

      Parameters:
      photo - the specified Photo
      Returns:
      the index that the photo is located at, or -1 if it does not exist.
